Here’s my honest take on what I loved and what I could’ve skipped during my Vietnam trip – no filters, just feels:

✅ Picks:
– The vibe at Train Street – totally worth the hype! 🚂
– Ba Na Hills was a whimsical escape – loved the craft beer break there once your wanna rest those tired feet🏰
– Vietnamese coconut iced coffee > egg coffee 🥥☕ (Pro tip: don’t miss the salted coffee – absolute sleeper hit!)
– Walking through Old Quarters – full of life, color, and culture.
– Bánh Mì 25 and Phở at Phở 10 – food goals unlocked. 🤤
– Definitely try the Bánh Xèo – crunchy, flavorful, unforgettable.
– The leather goods scene is worth a look – great finds, good prices in Hoi an👜
– Mỹ Khê Beach walk in Da Nang – like a tropical version of Miami 🌴
– Hội An is straight out of a postcard. I’d come back just to spend 1-2 nights more here 🌙✨
– Staying in Airbnbs in Hanoi & Da Nang – affordable and authentic!

❌ Misses:
– Stitching clothes in Hoi An – wasn’t impressed.
– The Alpine rollercoaster – fun but skippable.
– Grand World, Hanoi – didn’t quite hit the mark.
– Beer Street – one time experience. didn’t live up to the hype, especially when compared to Thailand’s buzzing nightlife 🍻
– Halong Bay day trip – underwhelming. I’d rather do the overnight cruise for the real magic.
– Overall, Thailand still wins when it comes to organized tours and nightlife experiences.

Vietnam gave me moments I’ll always cherish – and a few things I’d skip next time. That’s the beauty of travel 🌍💛
